{"name":"Mathlib.Data.Set.Pointwise.Iterate","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Data.Set.Pointwise.SMul","Mathlib.Algebra.Hom.Iterate","Mathlib.Dynamics.FixedPoints.Basic"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Set/Pointwise/Iterate.lean#L34-L47","name":"smul_eq_self_of_preimage_zpow_eq_self","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Pointwise/Iterate.html#smul_eq_self_of_preimage_zpow_eq_self","doc":"Let `n : ℤ` and `s` a subset of a commutative group `G` that is invariant under preimage for\nthe map `x ↦ x^n`. Then `s` is invariant under the pointwise action of the subgroup of elements\n`g : G` such that `g^(n^j) = 1` for some `j : ℕ`. (This subgroup is called the Prüfer subgroup when\n `G` is the `Circle` and `n` is prime.) "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Set/Pointwise/Iterate.lean#L28-L33","name":"vadd_eq_self_of_preimage_zsmul_eq_self","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Pointwise/Iterate.html#vadd_eq_self_of_preimage_zsmul_eq_self","doc":"Let `n : ℤ` and `s` a subset of an additive commutative group `G` that is invariant\nunder preimage for the map `x ↦ n • x`. Then `s` is invariant under the pointwise action of\nthe additive subgroup of elements `g : G` such that `(n^j) • g = 0` for some `j : ℕ`.\n(This additive subgroup is called the Prüfer subgroup when `G` is the `AddCircle` and `n` is\nprime.)"}]}